  "articleBody": "<!-- Page 5 --><article>\n\n\n      <h3 id=\"organisation-du-recit\" class=\"yellow\">organisation of the pictorial narrative around the legends of John the Baptist, John the Evangelist and the Old St John's Hospital</h3>\n\n        <h4 class=\"yellow\">a number of small scenes</h4>\n\n          <p>The narrative is structured around a number of <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">small scenes</span>\n          <ul>\n            <li>depicting <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">the two legends</span>,\n              <ul>\n                <li>of John the Baptist</li>\n                <li>and John the Evangelist</li>\n              </ul>\n            </li>\n            <li>and representing the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Crane's square</span> of Bruges linked to the St. John's Hospital.</li>\n          </ul>\n\n\n\n\n        <h4 class=\"yellow\">the narrative begins with the capitals of columns</h4>\n\n          <p>The two legends begin spatially with the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">sculpted scenes</span> above each saint in the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">column capitals</span>.</p>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, details of the central panel, from left to right: the four capitals, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, details of the central panel, from left to right: the four capitals, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-70-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"106\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/4-chapiteaux-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>details of the central panel, from left to right: the four capitals</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n\n\n        <h4 class=\"yellow\">the narrative continues with small scenes in the distance</h4>\n\n          <p>This manner of ordering the composition, which is found in many of Memling's other works, takes up the layout techniques of illumination <a id=\"note-7\" href=\"#renvoi-note-7\"><sup>note 7</sup></a>: the various scenes are tiered up to a very high placed horizon.</p>\n          <p>Small <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">scenes</span> take place in the distant <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">within the various framings</span> operated by the columns.</p>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/paysage-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, details of the central panel, “opening on the horizon”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, details of the central panel, “opening on the horizon”, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-diane-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"352\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/paysage-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>details of the central panel, “opening on the horizon”<br>on the left, scenes from the <cite>Legend of John the Baptist<cite>, on the right, those of John the Evangelist</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n\n\n        <h4 class=\"yellow\">the narrative concludes with each of the two inner shutters</h4>\n\n          <p>The narrative of the two legends then continues in each of the two inner panels.</p>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/2-volets-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, the right and left inner shutters: in the foreground on the left one, John the Baptist beheaded by Herod's order, on the right one, John the Evangelist in Patmos, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, the right and left inner shutters: in the foreground on the left one, John the Baptist beheaded by Herod's order, on the right one, John the Evangelist in Patmos, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"525\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/2-volets-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>the right and left inner shutters: in the foreground of the left one, John the Baptist beheaded by Herod's order, on the right one, John the Evangelist in Patmos</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n          <p>On each shutter, an episode forms <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">a main scene in the foreground</span>, completed in the narrative by <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">small scenes in the distance</span>.</p>\n          <ul>\n            <li>on the left inner shutter, <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">John the Baptist</span> has just been beheaded by <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Herod</span>'s order,</li>\n            <li>on the right inner shutter, <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">John the Evangelist</span> receives the «unveiling» of the text of <cite>The Revelation</cite> in <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Patmos</span>.</li>\n          </ul>\n\n\n\n\n        <h4 class=\"yellow\">Crane's square, symbolises the St. John hospital</h4>\n\n          <p>The view from the <ruby style=\"color:#e6a64d;\" lang=\"en\">Crane's&nbsp;square<rp>(</rp><rt style=\"color: #e6a64d;font-size: 70%;letter-spacing: 1px;\" lang=\"nl\">Kraanplaats</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby> and <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">St. John's Church</span>, in the background to the right of the drapery of honour behind the virgin, behind John the Evangelist refers directly to the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">religious</span> leaders of the hospital <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">sponsors of the work</span> and to the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">history</span> of the commissioning institution.</p>\n\n        <figure>\n          <picture><source sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-280.webp 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-380.webp 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-480.webp 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-640.webp 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-840.webp 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-1280.webp 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-1600.webp 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-1920.webp 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"/docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-640.jpg\" title=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, detail of the central panel, view of Crane's square and the St. John church, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" alt=\"Hans MEMLING, “Triptych of John the Baptist and John the Evangelist”, détail du panneau central, vue de la place de la Grue et l'église saint-Jean, Memling Museum, Old St. John's Hospital, Bruges (Brugge)\" class=\"class-40-img\" width=\"640\" height=\"757\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 98vw, (min-width: 959px) 50vw, 86vw\" srcset=\"\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-280.jpg 280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-380.jpg 380w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-480.jpg 480w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-640.jpg 640w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-840.jpg 840w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-1280.jpg 1280w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-1600.jpg 1600w,\n          /docs/saint-jean/place-de-la-grue-1920.jpg 1920w\"></picture><figcaption>detail of the central panel, view of Crane's square and the St. John church</figcaption>\n        </figure>\n\n          <p><span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">Two brothers from the hospital</span> are represented <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">measuring the imported bordeaux wine</span> arriving in Bruges.</p>\n          <p>This reminds us that the hospital was entrusted by the city around <time datetime=\"1300\">1300</time> with a <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">communal charge</span>, the <span style=\"color: #e6a64d;\">«right to gauge»</span> from which the institution had its income.</p>\n\n\n\n\n</article>"
